    "attributes": {
        "action": "Withdraw Government guidance giving police discretion for road traffic offences",
        "additional_details": "Keeping this current guidance in place allows police to turn a blind eye to road traffic offences. In Particular, pavement cycling offences and e-Scooter offences which break the law.\r\n\r\nDiscipline for people on e-scooters and cyclists who break the law and put pedestrians at risk needs equality to any other crime committed.",
        "background": "Remove Government guidance that allows the discretion of the police concerning road traffic offences.",
